'''Eom Ji-sung''' ({{Korean|hangul=엄지성}}; born 9 May 2002) is a South Korean [[Association football|footballer]] currently playing as a [[Midfielder (association football)#Winger|winger]] for {{English football updater|SwanseaC}} club [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

== Club career ==
In 2021, Eom joined the senior team of [[K League 1]] club [[Gwangju FC]]. He experienced relegation in his first professional season, but helped Gwangju win the [[K League 2]] the next year. After his contribution to the club's promotion was acknowledged, he was selected for the [[K League Best XI#K League 2 award (2013–present)|league's Best XI]] as well as the [[K League Young Player of the Year Award#K League 2 winners (2020–present)|Young Player of the Year Award]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gwangjufc.com/gwboard/gwboard_view.php?page=26&document_srl=76289&board_type=31&s_field=board_name&s_value=&board_statue=PUBLIC |script-title=ko:'어느 덧 3년차' 광주FC 엄지성이 바라보는 K리그1 |language=ko |publisher=Gwangju FC |date=2023-01-27 |access-date=2025-10-23}}</ref>

On 15 July 2024, Eom signed for [[EFL Championship]] club [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] on a four-year deal for an undisclosed fee,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.swanseacity.com/news/swansea-city-seal-signing-eom-ji-sung |title=Swansea City seal signing of Eom Ji-sung |publisher=Swansea City A.F.C |date=15 July 2024 |accessdate=15 July 2024}}</ref> reported to be in the region of £1 million by local media.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.walesonline.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/swansea-city-announce-eom-ji-29543543 |title=Swansea City announce Eom Ji-sung as second summer signing |publisher=Wales Online |last=Williams |first=Glen |date=15 July 2024 |accessdate=15 July 2024}}</ref> On 8 March 2025, he scored his first goal for the club against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Report {{!}} Swansea City 1 Middlesbrough 0 {{!}} Swansea |url=https://www.swanseacity.com/news/report-swansea-city-1-middlesbrough-0 |access-date=2025-06-16 |publisher=Swansea City A.F.C}}</ref> After his first season at Swansea City, he confessed his performances during the season did not satisfy himself and he had difficulty adapting to a large gap between the level of EFL Championship and K League. But he said he gradually felt his improvement and was finally motivated at the Championship.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://v.daum.net/v/20250518115518078 |script-title=ko:1년 차에 잉글랜드 무대 '안착' 엄지성 "힘들어 광주로 돌아가고 싶기도 했지만…EPL 향한 욕심 더 커졌다"[SS인터뷰] |language=ko |website=Daum |publisher=Sports Seoul |date=2025-05-18 |access-date=2025-10-23}}</ref>

== International career ==
In January 2022, Eom was selected for the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]] for the first time ahead of their off-season training.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-01-11 |script-title=ko:국가대표 첫 발탁 엄지성 "롤모델은 손흥민, 죽기살기로 뛸 것" |trans-title=National team's newcomer Eom Ji-sung: My role model is Son Heung-min. I will play with a do-or-die attitude. |url=https://www.donga.com/news/Sports/article/all/20220111/111188862/1 |access-date=2024-11-04 |publisher=The Dong-a Ilbo |language=ko}}</ref> In a friendly against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] on 15 January, he made his senior international debut and scored a goal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cho |first=Soo-jung |script-title=ko:엄지성 '헤더 득점'... 한국, 아이슬란드에 5-1 대승 |trans-title=Eom Ji-sung's "header goal"... South Korea won 5-1 over Iceland. |url=https://m.sports.naver.com/kfootball/article/003/0010946509 |language=ko |website=Naver |publisher=Newsis |date=2022-01-15 |access-date=2024-11-04}}</ref>

Eom was called up to the South Korea squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/south-korea-squad-world-cup-2026/blt15c57f5be1972d9b |title=South Korea squad World Cup 2026: Which players have made it to the showpiece in USA, Mexico and Canada? |publisher=Goal |date=2026-05-16 |access-date=2026-05-19}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
He enjoys playing one-on-one with the opposing defender due to his good sense of touch and dribbling skills. He receives the ball from the side and moves to the centre, preferring to play the role of a right-footed winger who mainly plays on the left.

